cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with improving the performance of convolutional neural networks for large-scale visual recognition tasks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The method proposed involves using second-order statistics (covariance) of high-level convolutional features, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on the ImageNet dataset, which is a popular benchmark in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
